      <div class="triangle-text">
        <div class="text-segment">
          <h4>GM (Grandmaster)</h4>
          <p>
            • Achieve a FIDE rating of 2500 or higher.<br>
            • Earn three GM norms in tournaments over at least 27 games.<br>
            • Alternative paths: Reach the final 16 in the FIDE World Cup, win the World Junior Championship (U20), win the World Senior Championship (50+ or 65+), or win a Continental championship.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="text-segment">
          <h4>IM (International Master)</h4>
          <p>
            • Achieve a FIDE rating of 2400 or higher.<br>
            • Earn three IM norms over 27 or more games.<br>
            • Alternative paths: Qualify for the FIDE World Cup, finish second/third in the World Junior Championship (U20) or World Senior Championship (50+ or 65+), win the World Youth Championship (U18/U16), finish in top places at Continental championships, or win a sub-Continental championship.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="text-segment">
          <h4>FM (FIDE Master)</h4>
          <p>
            • Achieve a FIDE rating of 2300 or higher.<br>
            • No norms are required.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="text-segment">
          <h4>CM (Candidate Master)</h4>
          <p>
            • Achieve a FIDE rating of 2200 or higher.<br>
            • No norms are required.<br>
            • Alternatives for players rated 2000–2199: Finish in the top three at the World Youth Championship (U8/U10), place in Continental U12/U14/U16 championships, or score 50%+ over at least 7 games at an Olympiad.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
  
  <!-- Women’s Titles Triangle Hierarchy -->
